rComments: Inspiriting professor. Relate the lecture material closely to the readings.
Lectures were inspiring, really fun to go to. Disorganized, but super engaging.

A superb professor.  The factors used to judge professors here don't do him justice.  He covers a lot of material without shying away from the real philosophical issues.  That makes it difficult to follow, but it is a small price to pay for the profundity of what you get in return.  The class was a highly satisfying experience.

People complained about the tests, but if you went to lecture and studied they were fine. Passage identifications were obvious, all you had to do match them to a philosopher's position (again, go to lecture).  Gave you the pool of essay questions for the tests in advance, which was helpful. Only downside was he was unorganised. Still a cool guy.

rComments: Engaging prof, I like his use of drug metaphors to explain concepts. Problem is his unrealistic expectations. 2 tests (midterm and final), with really hard essay questions and having to identify passages (which he made harder bc students did bad the first time..). Had no office hrs. Very obscure & difficult material. Would not recommend
